beyond scoring.

35:27.492 --> 35:29.290
Yeah, but Cedric grounded out
to the shortstop

35:29.360 --> 35:31.658
-- and was throw out at first by
quite a large margin. -- Yeah.

35:31.729 --> 35:34.221
Well, that is what is called
a routine ground ball.

35:34.299 --> 35:36.631
In your search for things
that are newsworthy,

35:36.701 --> 35:38.897
let the word "routine"
serve as a danger sign.

35:38.970 --> 35:40.563
There's nothing routine
about it.

35:40.638 --> 35:43.073
Casey, the guy's hitting .327
since the All-Star break,

35:43.141 --> 35:45.235
he has drawn <i>22</i> walks
in the leadoff position,

35:45.310 --> 35:46.869
and he's a threat
to steal second

35:46.945 --> 35:48.106
every time you put him on.

35:48.179 --> 35:49.669
He fouled off seven pitches.

35:49.747 --> 35:52.409
-- And you show each and every one of them.
-- You bet I do.

35:52.483 --> 35:55.214
We usually just show the pitch
that puts the ball into play.

35:55.286 --> 35:57.380
-- But then you miss the battle.
-- The battle?

35:57.455 --> 35:59.514
Yeah, he started him off
with a fastball up and in.

35:59.591 --> 36:01.252
Then slider away,
slider away,

36:01.326 --> 36:03.317
comes back with
a split-fingered change,

36:03.394 --> 36:06.056
drops the curve off the table,
sets him up off-speed,

36:06.130 --> 36:07.564
then jams him
high and tight.

36:07.632 --> 36:08.861
That's what got him out.

36:08.933 --> 36:10.924
It was a ground ball
to the shortstop.

36:11.002 --> 36:13.027
The inevitable conclusion
to a job well done.

36:13.104 --> 36:14.299
[Sighs deeply]

36:14.372 --> 36:17.137
We have 14 baseball games
to cover.

36:17.208 --> 36:18.141
Yeah.

36:18.209 --> 36:19.608
-- 30 seconds apiece.
-- Right.

36:19.677 --> 36:21.145
Your tape
is 8 1/2 minutes.

36:21.212 --> 36:22.373
I'm at a loss.

36:22.447 --> 36:24.142
You got to make it
shorter!

36:24.215 --> 36:25.410
I'm just not seeing it.

36:25.450 --> 36:28.511
